'''Matja<U+017E> Klop<U+010D>i<U+010D>''' (4 December 1934 &ndash; 15 December 2007) was a Slovenian [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]]. He directed 28 films between [[1959 in film|1959]] and [[2005 in film|2005]]. His film ''[[Dediscina]]'' was screened in the [[Un Certain Regard]] section at the [[1985 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name="festival-cannes.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/1137/year/1985.html |title=Festival de Cannes: Dediscina |accessdate=2009-06-28|work=festival-cannes.com}}</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[Dediscina]]'' (1984)
* ''[[My Dad, the Socialist Kulak]]'' (1987)

